results.content: How to save C20 buildings Events We are C20 Peabody’s Mid-C20 London Peabody’s Mid C20 London - 9.30am - 12.30pm | Saturday 11 May 2019　 Peabody has been providing high-quality homes for Londoners since 1862. In that year George Peabody, a wealthy American banker and philanthropist who had made London his home, launched the Peabody Donation Fund with the first of several gifts eventually amounting to half a million pounds. Join us for a tour of three Peabody mid-C20 estates in London. Christine Wagg and James McHugh are co-authors of the recently published book 'Homes for London: The Peabody Story' (Strathmore, 2018). Unfortunately, booking is closed for this event and we are no longer able to accept new bookings. Event List) Events Events policy
